The Board of Development Bank of Nigeria (DBN) will be asking its shareholders for permission to issue N100 billion bonds. To this end, the board of DBN will be holding an Extraordinary General Meeting (EGM) on Tuesday, January 25, 2022 in Abuja to get clearance to issue the bonds. At the EGM, DBN will also seek approval to borrow EUR 25,000,000 Green Credit line “by way of a Subordinated Loan Agreement for a 10-year tenure”.   UBA: Lifting promo winners with cash prizes     2021: Onne Customs generates N188.6b     Group get new secretary general   The bank will also apply for a grant of “EUR 500,000, from the KFW Development Bank, for on lending through Participating Financial Institutions, to the Micro, Small and Medium Scale Enterprises, for investment in renewable energy and energy-efficient products”. The public notice informing of the EGM stated that DBN will be asking shareholders: “to approve a N100,000,000,000 Medium-Term Notes Programme, authorising the bank, to issue from time to time, debt securities (“Bonds’), the aggregate nominal amount of which shall not exceed N100,000,000,000.00 (One Hundred Billion Naira). - Advertisement - The bank also wants shareholders “to approve the acceptance by the bank, of a EUR 25,000,000 Green Credit line by way of a Subordinated Loan Agreement for a 10-year tenure, and a grant of EUR 500,000, from the KFW Development Bank, for on lending through Participating Financial Institutions, to the Micro, Small and Medium Scale Enterprises, for investment in renewable energy and energy-efficient products”. Also in 2022, DBN will access N20,507,500,000 from the Multilateral/Bilateral projects-tied loans as contained in the 2022 budget.